r-spacing: 3px; margin-bottom: 10px; text-transform: uppercase;\">SIZE RELATIVE TO A 6-FT MAN:</dt></div>', '<h2 style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: GeoEditBold, &quot;Franklin Gothic Medium&quot;, &quot;Franklin Gothic&quot;, &quot;ITC Franklin Gothic&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 24px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.214; letter-spacing: 0.1px;\">What is a domestic dog?</h2><p style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); margin: 12px 0px 24px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 19px; font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; line-height: 1.632; letter-spacing: 0.1px;\">The term “domestic dog” refers to any of several hundred breeds of dog in the world today. While these animals vary drastically in appearance, every dog—from the Chihuahua to the Great Dane—is a member of the same species,&nbsp;<i style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; line-height: 1.632;\">Canis familiaris</i>. This separates domestic dogs from wild&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nationalgeographic.com/animals/mammals/facts/canines-canids\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); line-height: 28px; background-image: linear-gradient(120deg, rgb(255, 204, 0), rgb(255, 204, 0)); background-position: 0px 100%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-left: none; border-image: initial; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(255, 204, 0); color: inherit; cursor: pointer; transition: background-size 0.125s ease-in 0s; outline: 0px;\">canines</a>, such as coyotes, foxes, and wolves.</p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19px; letter-spacing: 0.1px;\">Domestic dogs are mostly kept as pets, though many breeds are capable of surviving on their own, whether it’s in a forest or on city streets. A third of all households worldwide have a dog, according to a 2016 consumer insights&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.gfk.com/insights/mans-best-friend-global-pet-ownership-and-feeding-trends\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; line-height: 28px; background-image: linear-gradient(120deg, rgb(255, 204, 0), rgb(255, 204, 0)); background-position: 0px 100%; background-repeat: no-repeat; background-size: 100% 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-left: none; border-image: initial; border-bottom: 2px solid rgb(255, 204, 0); color: inherit; cursor: pointer; font-size: 19px; transition: background-size 0.125s ease-in 0s; outline: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.1px;\">study</a><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 19px; letter-spacing: 0.1px;\">. This makes the domestic dog the most popular pet on the planet.</span><br></p>', 'dog-28306.jpg', 'dog-28306', NULL, '2024-02-10 23:19:20', NULL),
